article.description: Tucker Richardson had a season-high 20 points as Colgate edged past Holy Cross 74-70 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Richardson scores 20 to carry Colgate over Holy Cross 74-70
article.linkText: Richardson scores 20 to carry Colgate over Holy Cross 74-70
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- Tucker Richardson had a season-high 20 points as Colgate edged past Holy Cross 74-70 on Wednesday night. Richardson made 4 of 6 3-pointers. He added six assists. Will Rayman had 12 points for Colgate (16-10, 8-5 Patriot League). Jack Ferguson added 12 points. Rapolas Ivanauskas had 11 points for the visitors. Caleb Green had 19 points for the Crusaders (13-13, 4-9). Jacob Grandison added 13 points. Austin Butler had 12 points. Colgate takes on American on the road on Saturday. Holy Cross faces Bucknell at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
